{
  "description": {
    "title": "K-MSR: a credible decree + auction reserve INDUCES the investment the P0 market never makes",
    "paper": "PLANiT K-MSR working paper (July 2026), Sections 6-7 and Appendix A.10: the transition claim - an announced, credible reserve-price/decree package lowers the effective volatility the irreversible investor faces (sigma_eff = (1-q) * sigma), collapsing the Dixit-Pindyck hurdle from M(sigma=0.48) ~ 6.4 toward the pure timing wedge r/y ~ 1.83, while the auction reserve DELIVERS the trigger price (Results 2-3). This example solves that claim as an ENDOGENOUS equilibrium result (docs/invest-feedback-spec.md D1) instead of post-processing on an exogenous path - the gap the paper's Section 7 names.",
    "mechanism": "Both scenarios flag the same Steel H2-DRI option (theta = 5,000 KRW, y = 0.03, sigma = 0.48 - the paper's pooled KAU volatility estimate). 'P1 decree': hybrid decree MSR (price band 8,000-13,500 KRW, surplus band 2%-18%, 5 Mt/yr, 10 Mt pre-funded reserve) + a rising auction-reserve schedule 9,000 -> 12,800 KRW, and invest_credibility = 0.8 -> sigma_eff = 0.096, M ~ 2.124, trigger P* ~ 10,618 KRW. 'P0 no reserve': no MSR, no floor, credibility 0 -> M ~ 6.386, P* ~ 31,931 KRW. The adoption loop reads the DELIVERED (post-floor-clip) price path of the full banking solve each outer iteration.",
    "inputs": "6 years 2026-2031, caps 100 -> 75 Mt (derive_from_cap, no free allocation), 2 linear-MAC participants (Steel BAU 60 Mt slope 600; Power BAU 50 Mt slope 900), r = 5.5%, no initial bank, strict no-arbitrage off (floor-bound static years).",
    "expected_output": {
      "P0 delivered prices 2026-2031": [
        7055.7,
        7443.76,
        7853.17,
        8285.09,
        8740.77,
        9221.51
      ],
      "P1 delivered prices 2026-2031": [
        9000.0,
        9700.0,
        10400.0,
        11200.0,
        12000.0,
        12800.0
      ],
      "P1 adoption": "Steel/H2-DRI adopted 2029 - the first year the floor-delivered price (11,200) clears P* ~ 10,618; decree intake 5 Mt/yr in 2027-2028 (hybrid surplus signal) absorbs the early bank.",
      "P0 adoption": "NONE - the pure banking ramp tops out at ~9,222 KRW, a third of the uncredible trigger P* ~ 31,931.",
      "reading": "Same technology, same fundamentals: the decree package changes WHEN (and whether) the investment happens through two channels at once - the floor delivers the trigger price, and its credibility shrinks the option-value wedge. That is the paper's central transition mechanism, now a solved two-way equilibrium: the adopted capacity feeds back into the banking window it was priced on."
    },
    "run": "PYTHONPATH=src .venv/bin/python -m ets.cli --config examples/k_msr_decree_induces_investment.json"
